  The present invention relates to a system for updating a three-dimensional (3D) model of a luminal network inside a patient based on images of the luminal network. The system includes a computing device with a processor and memory, which stores instructions that, when executed by the processor, enable the following steps:
1. Accessing a 3D model of a luminal network inside a patient based on images of the luminal network;
2. Selecting a plurality of reference points within the 3D model of the luminal network;
3. Obtaining a plurality of survey points within the luminal network;
4. Dividing the 3D model of the luminal network into different regions of a lung;
5. Assigning a plurality of weights to the different regions of the lung;
6. Determining an alignment of the plurality of reference points with the plurality of survey points based on the plurality of weights; and
7. Generating a registration based on the alignment. The system provides a more accurate and efficient way of updating 3D models of luminal networks, which can be used in various medical applications such as diagnosis, treatment planning, and monitoring of lung diseases.
